-- Banca Popolare di Milano Says It Doesn't Need to Boost the Bank's Capital
-- Marco Bertacche
-- 2010-07-02T11:05:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-02/banca-popolare-di-milano-says-it-doesn-t-need-to-boost-the-bank-s-capital.html

          
          
             Banca Popolare di Milano said it
doesn’t need to boost capital. The bank said in a statement that
it’s internal reviews showed no need for fresh capital. The bank
said it hasn’t participated in any European stress tests. The
bank was commenting on a report in the Financial Times that it
needed to raise capital.  
